<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:187PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

<A STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;" HREF="#HRB2016043010K_HTM_SF745264ABAAFC0D4745DC32A5BA0102A">

	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

<DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:36PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	HRB Bank, as described above. These negative impacts were partially offset by our acquisition of franchisee businesses and favorable pricing and mix changes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="PADDING-TOP:8PX;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN; FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PX;">
</TD>
<TD>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;PADDING-LEFT:12PX;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#9642;
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;">
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Pretax earnings fell
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$173.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	23.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, due primarily to lower client volumes, operational impacts of BofI offering certain financial products and services, incremental marketing spend, and costs associated with changes to our capital structure including the divestiture of HRB Bank.
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
</TR>

<EFX_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS>
<A NAME="FIS_RESULTS_OF_OPERATIONS"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our subsidiaries provide assisted and DIY tax return preparation through multiple channels (including in-person, online and mobile applications, and desktop software) and distribute the H&amp;R Block-branded financial products and services of BofI. Tax returns are either prepared by H&amp;R Block tax professionals (in company-owned or franchise offices or virtually via the internet) or prepared and filed by our clients through our DIY tax solutions. We operate as a single segment that includes all of our continuing operations, which are designed to enable clients to obtain tax preparation services seamlessly.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Revenues decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$40.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, compared to the prior year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	U.S. assisted tax preparation fees increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, while royalty revenues declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$26.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	9.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. We acquired a number of franchisee businesses during the year, and declines in royalty revenues are due
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:-MOZ-RIGHT;" ALIGN="RIGHT">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:187PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:160PX;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:26PX;">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	H&amp;R Block, Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#160;| 2016 Form 10-K
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	23
</FONT>

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
<A NAME="eolPage26"></A>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<A STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;" HREF="#HRB2016043010K_HTM_SF745264ABAAFC0D4745DC32A5BA0102A">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</DIV>

<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	primarily to the associated loss of royalties when those businesses are acquired, and to a lesser extent a decline in client volumes served by franchise offices. The increase in U.S. assisted tax preparation fees is primarily the result of revenues from acquired franchise businesses and price increases, offset by a decline in tax returns prepared in company-owned offices. Return counts in our company-owned offices, excluding the impact of returns prepared in those offices resulting from acquired franchisee businesses, declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	6.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from the prior year. We acquired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	260
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;franchise offices in fiscal year 2016 and 350 franchise offices in fiscal year 2015. We expect to continue to acquire franchisee businesses in the future, but at levels below fiscal years 2016 and 2015.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	International tax preparation fees decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$17.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	8.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The decrease was driven by a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$23.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;decline resulting from unfavorable changes in foreign currency exchange rates, partially offset by favorable volume and price changes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Fees from our U.S. DIY business increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$2.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, as improved monetization for new and existing clients coupled with an increase in product attach rates were partially offset by a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;decrease in paid returns.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Fees earned on RTs decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to lower assisted return volumes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Revenues from H&amp;R Block Emerald Prepaid MasterCard
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#174;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;transactions decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	10.4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to our agreement with BofI and lower assisted return volumes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Revenue from fees for our POM is initially deferred, and recognized over the term of the service plan based on actual claims paid in relation to projected claims. Revenue increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$5.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	6.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to a change in projected claims that resulted in an increase in revenue recognized last year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Other revenues declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	19.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to the presentation of income from our mortgage loan portfolio and investments in AFS securities as other income in the current year rather than as revenue in the prior year. See Item 8,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Total operating expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$121.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	5.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, from the prior year. Total compensation and benefits decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$17.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;primarily due to a decline in short-term incentive compensation and the impact of changes in foreign currency exchange rates. Occupancy and equipment expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$29.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	7.9%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;increase in company-owned offices resulting from acquisitions of franchisee and competitor businesses. Marketing and advertising expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;due to planned increases in tax season spend, including our sweepstakes campaign. Depreciation and amortization expense increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$13.8 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	8.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to acquisitions of franchisee and competitor businesses. Other expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$76.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	28.8%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to costs totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$20.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;associated with capital transactions and the divestiture of HRB Bank, fees paid to BofI for products and services they offer to our clients, and increased litigation and consulting expenses.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Other income increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$16.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;primarily due to the inclusion of interest income on our mortgage loan portfolio and AFS securities (reported as revenue in the prior period), as discussed above and in Item 8, note 1 to the consolidated financial statements. Interest expense increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$23.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	52.4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, due primarily to issuance of our Senior Notes in September 2015 in the aggregate principal amount of $1.0 billion.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Pretax income for fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$173.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	23.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, over the prior year. The pretax margin decreased to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	18.7%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	24.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Net income from continuing operations declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$103.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	21.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;compared with the prior year. Diluted earnings per share from continuing operations decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	12.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from the prior year to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.53
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;due to a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	21.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;decline in net income, partially offset by a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	9.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;decline in weighted average shares outstanding.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The net loss from our discontinued operations totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$9.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for the current year, compared to a net loss of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$13.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in the prior year. Pretax losses of mortgage operations totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$18.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, compared to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$27.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in the prior year, and resulted primarily from litigation expenses and provisions related to SCC's estimated contingent losses for representation and warranty claims of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$4.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$16.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.

	Revenues increased

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$54.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	1.8%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, compared to fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. U.S. assisted tax preparation fees increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$71.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4.0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, while royalty revenues declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$23.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	7.4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, almost entirely due to acquisitions of franchisee businesses. Return counts in our company-owned offices, excluding returns prepared in those offices acquired during fiscal year 2015, declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	International tax preparation fees increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$7.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.8%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, due primarily to pricing changes, partially offset by unfavorable exchange rates.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Tax preparation fees from our U.S. DIY business increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	12.3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	8.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;increase in paid returns. The remaining increase was due to better monetization of new and existing clients and a higher number of more complicated returns.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Fees earned on RTs decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	5.7%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to lower assisted return volumes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Revenue from fees for our POM is initially deferred, and recognized over the term of the service plan based on actual claims paid in relation to projected claims. Revenue decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$8.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	9.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, in fiscal year 2015 primarily due to a change in projected claims that resulted in an increase in revenue recognized in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Total operating expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$78.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	3.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, from fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Total compensation and benefits increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;primarily due to higher variable field wages resulting from increased revenues and increased training costs. Occupancy and equipment expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2.9%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	4.6%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;increase in company-owned offices resulting from franchise acquisitions. Marketing and advertising expenses increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$34.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;due to a planned increase in national advertising. Depreciation and amortization expense increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$44.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	38.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to acquisitions of franchisee and competitor businesses and improvements to existing offices. Other expenses decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$37.6 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	12.4%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to lower litigation and consulting costs in the current year.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Other income declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$35.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, primarily due to a gain of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$18.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;on the sale of residual interests in mortgage securitizations and a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;gain on the sale of an intangible customer list, which were both recognized in fiscal year 2014. Interest expense declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$10.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	18.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, due to repayment of our Senior Notes that matured in October 2014. Other expenses declined
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;primarily due to an other-than-temporary impairment on AFS securities of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;recorded in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, coupled with a decline of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$12.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in foreign currency losses.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The net loss from our discontinued operations totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$13.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, compared to a net loss of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Pretax losses of mortgage operations totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$27.1 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, compared to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$38.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and resulted primarily from loss provisions related to SCC's estimated contingent losses for representation and warranty claims of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$16.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<A NAME="HRB2016043010K_HTM_S27B04C2FE99BB0DF4740C32A5E7DD4B8">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	DISCONTINUED OPERATIONS
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Discontinued operations include our discontinued mortgage operations.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CONTINGENT LOSSES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC has accrued a liability as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;for estimated contingent losses arising from representation and warranty claims of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$65.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The estimate of accrued loss is based on the best information currently available, significant management judgment, and a number of factors that are subject to change, including developments in case law and other factors, including those mentioned in "Critical Accounting Estimates" below. Changes in any one of these factors could significantly impact the estimate.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Losses may also be incurred with respect to various indemnification claims by underwriters, depositors, and securitization trustees in securitization transactions in which SCC participated. SCC has not concluded that a loss is probable or reasonably estimable related to these indemnification claims, therefore there is no accrued liability for these contingent losses as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	See additional discussion in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 1A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, "Risk Factors," "Critical Accounting Estimates" below and in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements.

<DIV>
<A NAME="HRB2016043010K_HTM_SADE1A79A01FE1E0E76B8C32A5E8DF351">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CRITICAL ACCOUNTING ESTIMATES
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We consider the estimates discussed below to be critical to understanding our financial statements, as they require the use of significant judgment and estimation in order to measure, at a specific point in time, matters that are inherently uncertain. Specific methods and assumptions for these critical accounting estimates are described in the following paragraphs. We have reviewed and discussed each of these estimates with the Audit Committee of our Board of Directors. For all of these estimates, we caution that future events rarely develop precisely as forecasted and estimates routinely require adjustment and may require material adjustment.
</FONT>
</DIV>

</TR>

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

<A NAME="eolPage29"></A>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<A STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;" HREF="#HRB2016043010K_HTM_SF745264ABAAFC0D4745DC32A5BA0102A">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	Table of Contents

<DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	See
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements, which discusses accounting policies and new or proposed accounting standards that may affect our financial reporting in the future.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	LOSSES ARISING FROM REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Nature of Estimates Required.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC accrues a liability for losses related to representation and warranty claims when those losses are believed to be both probable and reasonably estimable. Development of loss estimates is subject to a high degree of management judgment, and estimates may vary significantly period to period.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Assumptions and Approach Used.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC has entered into tolling agreements with counterparties that have made a significant portion of previously denied representation and warranty claims. While these tolling agreements remain in effect, they toll the running of any applicable statute of limitations related to potential lawsuits regarding representation and warranty claims and other claims against SCC.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC has engaged in discussions with these counterparties since fiscal year 2013 regarding the bulk settlement of previously denied and potential future representation and warranty and other claims against SCC. Based on settlement discussions with these counterparties, SCC believes a bulk settlement approach, rather than the loan-by-loan resolution process, will be needed to resolve all of the claims that are the subject of these discussions. On December 5, 2014, SCC entered into a settlement agreement to resolve certain of these claims. On December 18, 2015, SCC entered into settlement agreements with two additional counterparties to resolve certain additional claims, subject to the terms and conditions set forth in the settlement agreements. The amounts paid under the settlement agreements were fully covered by prior accruals. In the event that the ongoing efforts to settle are not successful, SCC believes claim volumes may increase or litigation may result.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC will continue to vigorously contest any request for repurchase when it has concluded that a valid basis for repurchase does not exist. SCC's decision whether to engage in bulk settlement discussions is based on factors that vary by counterparty or type of counterparty, and include the considerations (described below) used by SCC in determining its loss estimate.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC's loss estimate for representation and warranty claims is based on the best information currently available, significant management judgment, and a number of factors that are subject to change, including developments in case law and the factors mentioned below. These factors include the terms of prior bulk settlements, the terms expected to result from ongoing bulk settlement discussions, and an assessment of, among other things, historical claim results, threatened claims, terms and provisions of related agreements, counterparty willingness to pursue a settlement, legal standing of counterparties to provide a comprehensive settlement, bulk settlement methodologies used and publicly disclosed by other market participants, the potential pro-rata realization of the claims as compared to all claims, and other relevant facts and circumstances when developing its estimate of probable loss. SCC believes that the most significant of these factors are the terms expected to result from ongoing bulk settlement discussions, which have been primarily influenced by the bulk settlement methodologies used and publicly disclosed by other market participants, and the anticipated pro-rata realization of the claims of particular counterparties as compared to the anticipated realization if all claims and litigation were resolved together with payment of SCC's related administration and legal expense. Changes in any one of the factors mentioned above could significantly impact the estimate.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sensitivity of Estimate to Change.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;It is reasonably possible that future losses related to representation and warranty claims may vary from the amounts accrued for these exposures. SCC currently believes the aggregate range of reasonably estimable possible losses in excess of amounts accrued is not material. This estimated range is based on the best information currently available, significant management judgment and a number of factors that are subject to change, including developments in case law and the factors mentioned above. The actual loss that may be incurred could differ materially from our accrual or the estimate of reasonably possible losses.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	SCC has accrued a liability as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, for estimated contingent losses arising from representation and warranty claims of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$65.3 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. SCC accrued incremental loss provisions of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$16 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$25 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal year 2014.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	If the amount that SCC is ultimately required to pay with respect to claims and litigation related to its past sales and securitizations of mortgage loans, together with payment of SCC's related administration and legal expense, exceeds SCC's net assets, the creditors of SCC, or a bankruptcy trustee if SCC were to file or be forced into bankruptcy,
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;TEXT-ALIGN:-MOZ-RIGHT;" ALIGN="RIGHT">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:187PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;COLOR:#FFFFFF;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
<A STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;" HREF="#HRB2016043010K_HTM_SF745264ABAAFC0D4745DC32A5BA0102A">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</DIV>

<DIV>

</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	may attempt to assert claims against us for payment of SCC's obligations. Claimants may also attempt to assert claims against or seek payment directly from the Company even if SCC's assets exceed its liabilities. SCC's principal assets, as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, total approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$386 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and consist primarily of an intercompany note receivable. We believe our legal position is strong on any potential corporate veil-piercing arguments; however, if this position is challenged and not upheld, it could have a material adverse effect on our business and our consolidated financial position, results of operations and cash flows.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	The accrued liability does not include potential losses related to litigation and indemnification matters discussed in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 1A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, "Risk Factors" and in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements. Also see
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	LITIGATION AND RELATED CONTINGENCIES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Nature of Estimates Required.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;We accrue liabilities related to certain legal matters for which we believe it is probable that a loss has been incurred and the amount of such loss can be reasonably estimated. Assessing the likely outcome of pending or threatened litigation, including the amount of potential loss, if any, is highly subjective.&#160;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Assumptions and Approach Used.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;We are subject to pending or threatened litigation claims and indemnification claims, which are described in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Item 8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements. It is our policy to routinely assess the likelihood of any adverse judgments or outcomes related to legal matters, as well as ranges of probable losses. A determination of the amount of the liability required to be accrued, if any, for these contingencies is made after analysis of each known issue and an analysis of historical experience. In cases where we have concluded that a loss is only reasonably possible or remote, or is not reasonably estimable, no liability is accrued.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sensitivity of Estimate to Change.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;It is reasonably possible that future litigation and related contingent losses may vary from the amounts accrued. For some matters where a liability has not been accrued, we are able to estimate a reasonably possible loss or range of loss. Those matters for which an estimate is not reasonably possible are not included within this estimated range. Therefore, this estimated range of reasonably possible loss represents what we believe to be an estimate of reasonably possible loss only for certain matters meeting these criteria. It does not represent our maximum loss exposure. For those matters, and for matters where a liability has been accrued, as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, we believe the aggregate range of reasonably possible losses in excess of amounts accrued is not material. However, our judgments on whether a loss is probable, reasonably possible or remote and our estimates of probable loss amounts may differ from actual results due to difficulties in predicting the outcome of jury trials, arbitration hearings, settlement discussions and related activity, predicting the outcome of class certification actions and numerous other uncertainties. Due to the number of claims which are periodically asserted against us, and the magnitude of damages sought in those claims, actual losses in the future may significantly differ from our current estimates.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	INCOME TAXES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;&#8211;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Nature of Estimates Required.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;The income tax laws of jurisdictions in which we operate are complex and subject to different interpretations by the taxpayer and applicable government taxing authorities. Income tax returns filed by us are based on our interpretation of these rules. The amount of income taxes we pay is subject to ongoing audits by federal, state and foreign tax authorities, which may result in proposed assessments, including assessments of interest or penalties. We have accrued a liability for uncertain tax positions that reflects our judgment as to the ultimate resolution of the applicable issues if subject to judicial review or other settlement.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Assumptions and Approach Used.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;We evaluate each uncertain tax position based on its technical merits. If we determine it is more likely than not a tax position will be sustained based on its technical merits, we record the impact of the position in our consolidated financial statements at the largest amount that is greater than fifty percent likely of being realized upon ultimate settlement. We do not record a tax benefit for tax positions where we have concluded it is not more likely than not to be sustained. Differences between a tax position taken or expected to be taken in our tax returns and the amount of benefit recognized and measured in the financial statements result in unrecognized tax benefits, which are recorded in the balance sheet as either a liability for unrecognized tax benefits or reductions to recorded tax assets, as applicable.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sensitivity of Estimate to Change.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Our assessment of the technical merits and measurement of tax benefits associated with uncertain tax positions is subject to a high degree of judgment and estimation. Actual results may
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:187PX;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">
<TR>
<TD COLSPAN="2">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:26PX;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:160PX;">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">
<DIV STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:8PT;BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000;COLOR:#FFFFFF;">
	28
</FONT>
</DIV>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:MIDDLE;PADDING-LEFT:2PX;PADDING-TOP:2PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:2PX;PADDING-RIGHT:2PX;">

	2016 Form 10-K |

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	differ from our current judgments due to a variety of factors, including changes in law, interpretations of law by taxing authorities that differ from our assessments, changes in the jurisdictions in which we operate and results of routine tax examinations. We believe we have adequately provided for any reasonably foreseeable outcome related to these matters. However, our future results may include favorable or unfavorable adjustments to our estimated tax liabilities in the period the assessments are made or resolved, or when statutes of limitation on potential assessments expire. As a result, our effective tax rate may fluctuate on a quarterly basis.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, we accrued liabilities for unrecognized tax benefits on uncertain tax positions of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$112 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. Of the total gross unrecognized tax benefit as of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$82 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;would impact our effective tax rate if ultimately recognized.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	INCOME TAXES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	&#32;VALUATION OF DEFERRED TAX ASSETS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Nature of Estimates Required.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;We account for income taxes under the asset and liability method, which requires us to record deferred income tax assets and liabilities for future tax consequences attributable to differences between the financial statement carrying value of existing assets and liabilities and their respective tax basis. Deferred taxes are determined separately for each tax-paying component within each tax jurisdiction based on provisions of enacted tax law.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We record a valuation allowance to reduce our deferred tax assets to the estimated amount that we believe is more likely than not to be realized. Determination of a valuation allowance for deferred tax assets requires that we make judgments about future matters that are not certain, including projections of future taxable income and evaluating potential tax-planning strategies.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Assumptions and Approach Used.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Our deferred tax assets include state and foreign tax loss carry-forwards, which in some cases have been reduced by a valuation allowance. We have considered taxable income in carry-back periods, historical and forecasted earnings, future taxable income, the mix of earnings in the jurisdictions in which we operate, and tax planning strategies in determining the need for a valuation allowance and the estimated amount of these deferred tax assets that will more likely than not be realized.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sensitivity of Estimate to Change.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;To the extent that actual results differ from our current assumptions, valuation allowances for deferred tax assets will increase or decrease. In the event we determine that we could not realize all or part of our deferred tax assets in the future, an adjustment would be charged to earnings in the period in which we make such determination. Likewise, if we later determine it is more likely than not that we could realize the deferred tax assets, we would reverse the applicable portion of the previously provided valuation allowance.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	As of April 30,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, valuation allowances for our deferred tax assets totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$22 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. As a result of changes in deferred tax valuation allowances, our effective tax rate decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	0.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	0.2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<A NAME="HRB2016043010K_HTM_SABE57703498C09BD5C7BC32A5E9CBBD7">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

	NEW ACCOUNTING PRONOUNCEMENTS
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

</FONT>

<EFX_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL>
<A NAME="FIS_LIQUIDITY_CAPITAL"></A>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CAPITAL RESOURCES AND LIQUIDITY
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;&#8211;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	OVERVIEW
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#8211; Our primary sources of capital and liquidity include cash from operations (including changes in working capital), draws on our 2015 CLOC, and issuances of debt. We use our sources of liquidity primarily to fund working capital, service and repay debt, pay dividends, repurchase shares of our common stock, and acquire businesses.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Our operations are highly seasonal and substantially all of our revenues and cash flow are generated during the period from January through April. Therefore, we require the use of cash to fund losses from May through December, and typically rely on available cash balances from the prior tax season and borrowings to meet our off-season liquidity needs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Operating Activities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Cash provided by operating activities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	decreased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$94.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;from fiscal year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. The decrease from the prior year was primarily due to lower net income and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$88.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in settlement payments related to representations and warranties, partially offset by a decline in income taxes paid of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$71.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Investing Activities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Cash provided by investing activities totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$329.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;compared to cash used of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$148.9 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in the prior year. This change is principally due to sales of investment securities totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$436.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;resulting primarily from our decision to sell substantially all AFS securities following the divestiture of HRB Bank. In addition, there was a decrease of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$24.5 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in payments for business acquisitions, and a decrease of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$23.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in capital expenditures.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Financing Activities.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Cash used in financing activities increased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$1.3 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	. As described more fully below, changes in cash from financing activities resulted primarily from share repurchase activity and changes in customer deposit balances including the sale of deposits to BofI, partially offset by the issuance of new debt.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CASH REQUIREMENTS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;&#8211;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Dividends and Share Repurchase.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;Returning capital to shareholders in the form of dividends and the repurchase of outstanding shares has historically been a significant component of our capital allocation plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	We have consistently paid quarterly dividends. Dividends paid totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$201.7 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$220.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	$219.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;in fiscal years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, respectively. Although we have historically paid dividends and plan to continue to do so, there can be no assurances that circumstances will not change in the future that could affect our ability or decisions to pay dividends.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In September 2015, we announced that our Board of Directors approved a new
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$3.5 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;share repurchase program, effective through June 2019. As a part of the repurchase program, in the current year, we purchased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$2.0 billion
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;of our common stock at an average price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$35.46
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;per share. See Item 8,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	note 10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;to the consolidated financial statements for additional information. Although we may continue to repurchase shares, there is no assurance that we will purchase up to the full board authorization.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Divestiture of HRB Bank.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;At the time of the closing of the P&amp;A Transaction, we made a one-time cash payment to BofI of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$419 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	, which was approximately equal to the carrying value of the liabilities (including all deposit liabilities) assumed by BofI. In connection with the closing, we liquidated the AFS securities previously held by HRB Bank and received proceeds of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$388 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;on the sale.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	In connection with the P&amp;A Transaction we entered into the RPA dated August 31, 2015 with BofI. Pursuant to the RPA, we are required to purchase a 90% participation interest, at par, in all EAs originated by BofI throughout the term of the RPA. At April 30, 2016 the principal balance of purchased participation interests totaled
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	$13.4 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:24PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	See additional discussion in Item 1, under "Recent Developments," and in Item 8,

	note 2
</FONT>
